	<h1>Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m01.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans</em> is a silent romantic drama film directed by F. W. Murnau, starring George O&#39;Brien, Janet Gaynor, and Margaret Livingston.</p>

		<p>William Fox produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Fox Film Corporation on September 23, 1927, with a runtime of 95 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $200,000 (estimated) and made $121,107  at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $3.4 million and $2 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Carl Mayer, with Hugo Riesenfeld composing the filmâ€™s music. Charles Roshner and Karl Struss oversaw cinematography, and Harold Schuster helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/sunrise-a-song-of-two-humans-f.-w.-murnau-1927">View an archived version of <em>Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunrise:_A_Song_of_Two_Humans">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans</em>.</a></p>

